Description: Using PEG to prevent PEG induced anaphylaxis PROBLEM: PEGylated drugs are a mainstay in medicine, and PEG allergy greatly increases treatment costs. In some cases, the PEGylated drug represents the last-line of treatment, such as PEG-uricase for treatment of chronic tophaceous refractory gout. In other cases (e.g. pegaspargase (PEG-ASNase; for treatment of acute lymboblastic leukemia), the PEG-drug represents part of the most effective treatment regimen. For many PEGylated drugs, there are no viable alternative treatments. Unfortunately, with a number of PEGylated drugs, anti-PEG antibodies (APA) can be readily induced in humans that leads to loss of efficacy and increased risk of infusion reactions (IR), including anaphylaxis. For instance, APA is directly responsible for loss of efficacy in ~50% of patients treated with Krystexxa (PEG-uricase), with IR observed in ~60% of APA+ patients. Similarly, APA is directly responsible for loss of efficacy in ~40% of the patients treated with Oncospar (PEG-asparaginase). In other cases, such as Palynziq (PEGvaliase; for treatment of phenylketonuria), APA is induced in 100% of patients, and is directly responsible for a black box warning for anaphylaxis. SOLUTION: The underlying technology is the use of high molecular weight free PEG (MW >20 kDa), to be given either before or used in conjunction with PEGylated drugs that are at risk of inducing APA, or PEGylated drugs given to patients with already established high titers of APA. We have shown that this can effectively reduce APA, restore prolonged circulation of PEGylated drugs despite repeated dosing, and reduce allergic reactions to PEGylated drugs.

Description: "Population Services International (PSI) is a global nonprofit organization focused on the encouragement of healthy behavior and affordability of health products. PSI was founded in 1970 to improve reproductive health using commercial marketing strategies and has expanded to work in over 50 countries in the areas of malaria, family planning, HIV, diarrhea, pneumonia and sanitation. PSI is headquartered in Washington, DC. "A hallmark of PSI is a commitment to the principle that health services and products are most effective when they are accompanied by robust communications and distribution efforts that help ensure wide acceptance and proper use. "PSI works in partnership with local governments, ministries of health and local organizations to create health solutions that are built to last." (website, 1/2/2017)
Comments (Public): PSI?s tax ID number is 56-0942853 Philip Harvey, a former CPC graduate research assistant, and Dr. Timothy Black began PSI in 1970 with the goal of improving health around the world for poor and at-risk populations in less developed countries. PSI's core values are stated as "bottom line health impact, private sector speed and efficiency, decentralization, innovation and entrepreneurship, and a long-term commitment to the people [they] serve," and reflect their goal to combine the strengths of the private sector with the ideals of a nonprofit. In the beginning, the organization worked primarily in the family planning sector, using commercial marketing strategies to sell products at subsidized prices. PSI has since branched out and now works to promote health programs dealing with HIV/AIDS, safe water, malaria, and nutrition. In 2006, PSI's headquarters are in Washington and London, and its projects employ over 7,000 people in 60 countries.

" "Re-Dazzle is a credible, online market for jewelry enthusiasts who demand the utmost in quality and security in exchanging their treasures. Unlike other sites, Re- Dazzle uses certified American Gem Society jewelers for authentication and logistical services to gain consumers? trust. Re- Dazzle provides a trusted method for both buyers and sellers to maximize the value and spirit of each piece of jewelry. "Re- Dazzle?s website is the hub for the online jewelry transactions. Using both B2B and B2C channels of distribution, Re-Dazzle builds networks, relationships, and revenue streams through four main components; buyer, seller, AGS Jeweler, and Re- Dazzle. A seller will take their unwanted jewelry to an AGS certified jeweler who, for a fee dependent on the piece?s estimated value, will authenticate and evaluate the piece and place it on the website. A buyer will purchase the piece from the website for the list price. After receiving the payment from the buyer, Re- Dazzle will send payment less commission to the seller, and split the commission (based on a tiered structure) with the retail jeweler." Description: At SenterME, we are on a mission to revolutionize emotional wellness for women professionals. We don't just offer a solution; we craft an immersive journey, a transformative adventure designed to empower women to conquer life's demands while nurturing their emotional well-being. What sets SenterME apart is our commitment to providing more than just a conventional emotional wellness platform. We've innovatively curated a holistic experience that blends personalized pathways, immersive learning experiences, and a supportive community, offering a refreshing departure from the one-size-fits-all approach. Our platform is not merely a set of tools; it's a companion in the journey toward self-discovery, growth, and lasting emotional wellness. We leverage cutting-edge technology to create a space where women can explore, learn, and thrive at their own pace, integrating joy and positivity into every facet of their emotional well-being. What's truly groundbreaking is our fusion of diverse content formats?captivating stories, interactive exercises, mindfulness practices, thought-provoking podcasts, and soul-soothing meditations?all meticulously designed to resonate with individual needs and preferences. The result is an endorphin-boosting approach that not only educates but elevates the spirit. But it doesn't stop there. SenterME goes beyond the ordinary by fostering a vibrant community where like-minded women can connect, share insights, and uplift each other. This sense of camaraderie is integral to our vision of making emotional wellness a shared and celebrated journey. In essence, SenterME isn't just a platform; it's a movement. It's a realization that emotional wellness is not a destination but a continuous, joyous expedition?a journey we're excited to embark on with every woman seeking a more empowered and fulfilling life.

Description: Skalara's AI engine can generate and distribute tasks based on project descriptions and employee skills. Additional features or changes are easily implemented, with the AI generating new tasks and seamlessly integrating them into the workflow. Detailed Sub-Task Generation: Within each feature generated, Skalara?s AI creates relevant tasks. If a generated task is too broad, the user can generate sub-tasks, allowing for atomic control over the steps taken to complete a project. Intelligent Team Assignments: Our platform focuses on your team's strengths and assigns tasks based on individual team members' past performances, ensuring efficiency and smooth workflows. While there are several prominent players in the project management arena, such as Asana, Jira, and ClickUp, our approach differentiates us in two significant ways: our user personas and our inherent integration of AI. Many established platforms market themselves as all-encompassing solutions suitable for various teams across different sectors. Though this broad approach has served them well, it allows us to carve out a specialized niche. By centering our attention on small tech teams and indie developers, we can address specific challenges and nuances this segment faces, which broad-spectrum platforms may overlook. In other words, we are a vertical startup while our competitors are horizontal. This niche focus enables the second, and perhaps the more vital, differentiation: our AI-driven foundation. Rather than treating AI as an added feature, we've embedded it at the core of our platform. This allows for optimized task generation tailored to tech teams and developers. Generalized platforms aiming to cater to every team type would struggle to integrate such AI capabilities because AI, by its nature, excels when given a specific context and can hallucinate when given ambiguous data

"A non-profit extension of Teach Tech called the Teach Tech Foundation will also help to improve the lives of low-income seniors. The main company will invest 50% of all profits earned into this foundation, which will purchase laptops and Kindles to be distributed to low-income retirement and nursing homes. Furthermore, this extension of the company will pay students to teach members of low-income homes the same lessons that are taught at the higher-income, profitable communities, in order to improve the lives of seniors who would otherwise be unable to pay for the service." Description: Problem: Solar assets have been underperforming financial models for 10 years in a row, costing stakeholders billions of dollars in missed revenue. This is due to data silos and lack of high-quality, low-cost, open and transparent data marketplaces in the solar industry. Solution: The SunDAO Network = A dynamic data as a service platform for the solar industry to locate, buy, sell, store and monetize solar data Essential Components: A) Solar Data Marketplace; B) Solar Data Ledger or storage back-end based on blockchain technology and Google / IBM cloud C) Solar App Store, which includes our custom solar-data-trained AI chatbot = ?SunnyGPT? and our Unreal engine based game-as-a-service, Metaverse Solar (www.metaversesolar.io). Our team's mission is to unlock solar data silos at scale for industry-best outcomes for Asset Owners, Insurers and Financiers. We are building a trusted, open-source data normalization/validation algorithm, providing a secure data storage environment, and empowering data owners to anonymize and de-identify their data to feed a massive solar data lake where "data takers" are able to buy, query, request, and obtain high-quality, low-cost solar data to improve outcomes. Sustainable Business Model: 1) Subscription fees: Insurers, developers, OEMs, incumbents such as WoodMac, industry consortiums, financiers and others pay for data and analytic insights. 2) Revenue-share: Marketplace fees and data monetization commissions 3) App store: Build, licenses and sells apps (i.e. AI ?SunnyGPT?, risk assessment and financial tools) 4) Data services: Revenue from data services (i.e. brokering, validating) Go to Market: Initially the Southeastern US, with over 18 GW of operating solar assets and 40 GW anticipated by 2026. Our team's co-founders have spent our entire careers in this region and have deep roots and wide networks in the power industry throughout the US Southeast.
Comments (Public): Incorporated under Blockchain Power, LLC in NC (Tiffany, 6-18-24) From their Launch application: "We have over $200M in active grant submissions in to Department of Energy, Department of Defense, and private foundations. We are eager to connect formally with UNC through the Launch Chapel Hill program to begin working collaboratively at the intersection of energy, data and compute power."

Description: In simple terms, my company is a standard concession stand that serves cotton candy, sno-cones, shaved ice, popcorn, funnel cakes, fried treats (oreos, milky ways, twinkies, funnel fries), pretzels, and cinnamon glazed nuts. What makes us different is that we can customize our products to match themes for different venues. For example, the Bigfoot Festival in Marion NC accepted us as a funnel cake vendor. For this event, we met with a metalworker, who was able to design a foot-shaped funnel cake ring concept, allowing for Big Foot Funnel Cake Prints (also will be used at UNC events for the Tar Heel Cakes). Unfortunately, the festival was rained out, so the product has not been tested. Additionally, our small business allows us to cut the middle man out, like munchees, to deliver fresh food, usually cheaper than the prepackaged products. While we still do deliveries, freshness is a higher priority than other businesses most sports venues use. We also operate as a mobile business, allowing us to cater to smaller events around the counties we serve. We have done weddings in Greensboro and Salisbury, as well as the City of Concord Christmas Parade.

Description: We effectively connect student workers with companies that require or desire student labor and sales. We are creating a web application that connects student workers with businesses based upon four metrics, availability, likeability, social media acumen, and to a lesser extent industry experience. No other competitor has designed a labor application that matches the scheduling needs of the employer with the scheduling needs of the student. We've designed a process in which students will put in their availability and will then search for opportunities through that availability. The search function will return opportunities with a percentage match attached to each that tells the student how well this opportunity matches up with their own schedule. The same process happens for businesses as they enter in the needed shifts and hours for the opportunity and when they search for students they get a percentage match list back for students that fit into that opportunity's scheduling needs well.
Comments (Public): Incorporated NC participating in NC IDEA LABS starting June 2019
Comments (Private): NC Sec of State says company is dissolved 12/17/20. JL (7/5/20).

Description: VADE is a single comprehensive parking spot marketplace. By using beacon technology and an intuitive mobile app, users can find open spots in real time, and pay for those spots without leaving their vehicle. This will save users, even in Chapel Hill save at least 17 hours a year (on average) looking for parking. VADE will provide a single source for street, lot, and residential spots sourced from governments, institutions, and a peer- to-peer network where users can list their private spots to earn money. By connecting the individual beacons to centralized hubs and a single server, VADE can provide clients with real time and historical data analytics to make more informed business decisions. Not only will clients know exactly what spots are open, occupied, or taken illegally, but they will also gain better insight into user habits that determine their pricing strategies. This enhanced connectivity and data analytics will pave the way to the more digital future moving forward, this type of infrastructure will play a pivotal role in the development of smart cities around the world.

Description: The need for high quality, effective, dual language curriculum is tremendous. After converting Chapel Hill?s Frank Porter Graham Elementary School into a dual language school, we struggled to find curriculum that was written to support bilingual and biliterate proficiency, and we were forced to write our own. After talking with many other dual language schools and going to many dual language conferences, we realized this is a large problem across America. Schools are very eager to purchase curriculum to be taught in the classroom, but there is very little that exists for the dual language schools, and what is out there is poor in quality. We created the Viva Biliteracy blog to see what traction we could get, and we were pleasantly surprised by the web traffic and user registrations. At a conference, we pitched the idea of developing curriculum units and packaging this for sale to other K-5 schools while providing professional development sessions to complement those units and other instructional needs. There was tremendous support, and we constantly have administrators, coaches, and teachers from other schools and conferences across the United States asking, ?May we buy them from you??

Description: "Thorp founded Xanthon Inc. in 1996 with Jim Skinner and Carson Loomis. Xanthon represents an effort by the university to recognize strong potential in Thorp?s invention as the basis for a new company. UNC-CH helped develop Xanthon?s business plan, negotiate a licensing agreement and select North Carolina-based investors to support the new company. Xanthon is developing a diagnostic kit for genetically detecting cancers and hundreds of different infectious agents. It is based on an invention by Thorp that represented a new method of genetic diagnostics using advanced electrochemistry to detect DNA and identify its structure. In Thorp?s technique, special compounds called mediators are used to carry electrons from DNA or RNA, another nucleic acid, to electrodes, producing an electrical signal that indicates the presence and quantity of a genetic material. Such testing is expected to be cheaper, faster and more reliable than conventional diagnostics." (UNC news article of 2/2000, 1/12/2016)

Description: Yoomi is developing a software platform to address the largest problems that physical therapists face, namely a lack of patient motivation and buy-in to home exercise programs, and an inability for physical therapists to adequately support their patients once they leave the practice. Yoomi addresses these issues by providing a web platform that extends physical therapy treatment into the home, and enables patients to receive guidance on their exercise form through gamified workouts in front of a phone or laptop camera. Data from the workout is also collected in order to help physical therapists make better decisions regarding treatment and care, and help patients improve their form over time. By offering an exciting experience that guides patients to perform their exercises correctly and safely, physical therapists can improve patient outcomes (and receive higher insurance reimbursement through MIPS), decrease patient visit times, attract more patients, and increase patient engagement rates. Currently, there is no solution on the market that provides real-time feedback on patient home exercise form without the need for hardware sensors. Yoomi offers a zero hardware solution, and therefore maximizes accessibility and cuts costs. Further, Yoomi?s decision to target healthcare professionals as opposed to the direct-to-consumer market will enable Yoomi to develop credibility by leveraging the current healthcare system, allowing Yoomi to develop a stronger brand than its competitors such as Hinge and SWORD, which have chosen to target the direct-to-consumer market. Yoomi?s heavy emphasis on gamification aims to enable PTs to keep their patients better engaged than any other product on the market. Finally, Yoomi enables PTs to adjust a workout?s sets, reps, required range of motion, speed, and patient posture with Yoomi?s flexible computer vision technology to completely tailor workouts to each patient?s needs.
Comments (Public): maybe incorporated DE as Yoomi Health Inc on 3/16/2022 (Cindy, 5/10/2022), confirmed active (Patrick, 6/24/2022). Website is still active (Mackenzie, 6/27/23). 'Yoomi Health' listed on DE SoS website, website active, email updated (4-1-24- John).
